From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] privacy: disable the built-in password manager by default

Disables Chromium's built-in password manager (save password prompts,
autofill from the built-in store) by default. Fennec recommends using
Bitwarden or the OS native keychain instead.

Rationale:
  - The built-in manager syncs to Google Account when sync is enabled;
    Fennec disables sync by default but the surface still exists.
  - External password managers have stronger audit trails and portability.
  - Fennec's Settings → Privacy shows a clear recommendation with links.

Users can re-enable via Settings → Privacy → Password manager.
Existing saved passwords are preserved — this only disables new saves
and autofill prompts.

PILLAR: Privacy
JOURNAL: none

---
 chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc b/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
index 3e4f5d6a..5b6c7d8e 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
@@ -435,6 +435,12 @@ void ProfileImpl::RegisterProfilePrefs(
+  // Fennec: disable built-in password save prompts by default.
+  // PasswordManager::IsSavingEnabled() reads kCredentialsEnableService.
+  registry->RegisterBooleanPref(
+      password_manager::prefs::kCredentialsEnableService,
+      false,
+      user_prefs::PrefRegistrySyncable::SYNCABLE_PREF);
+  // Also disable autofill from the built-in store.
+  registry->RegisterBooleanPref(
+      password_manager::prefs::kCredentialsEnableAutosignin,
+      false,
+      user_prefs::PrefRegistrySyncable::SYNCABLE_PREF);
 }
